/*
try...catch

it’s used to handle runtime errors in JavaScript so your app doesn’t crash.
SYNTAX--->
try {
  // code that may throw error
} catch (err) {
  // handle error
} finally {
  // always runs (optional)
}

How It Works (Important)
Code inside try runs
If error occurs 👉 execution jumps to catch
Remaining code in try is skipped
finally always runs (if present)
try...catch only works for synchronous code for asynchronus you have to maske some changes------->NOTE

AND for asynchronus code
.catch() → Promise errors
try/catch → with await
fetch needs -> manual error check
Promise.all -> fails fast
allSettled -> is safer
*/
