Debounce
What it does

👉 Waits until no event happens for a given time, then runs function

🔹 Where to Use Debounce

example ==>
    function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timer;

  return function (...args) {
    clearTimeout(timer); // cancel previous

    timer = setTimeout(() => {
      fn.apply(this, args);
    }, delay);
  };
}
  Only last call executes

debouncedFn(1);
debouncedFn(2);
debouncedFn(3);

👉 Output:

3

